an substantive characteristics, such as actually learning something. Grading becomes more important for its social consequences than for its pedagogical uses. For these and other reasons, the pursuit of certification and degrees takes precedence over the goals of learning, and the private benefits of schooling take precedence over its democratic and civic functions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEducationzAims and objectiveszUnited States. 0aEducation, SecondaryzUnited States. 0aEducational equalizationzUnited States. 0aSchool creditszUnited States. 0aSchool management and organizationzUnited States. 0aSocial mobilityzUnited States. 0aTeachersxTraining ofxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aTeachingxSocial aspectszUnited States. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030015944840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300159448423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300159448/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles